      {
        "turn": 23,
        "message": "[GM] Uneventful night. Morning wake-up. Long rest: all members HP/MP full.",
        "narrative": "The night was quiet.\n\nThe mana wire vibrated faintly a couple of times, but it was only small wild animals passing through. The campfire gradually died down, and stars filled the sky.\n\nAt shift change, Lucena approached Noel and whispered softly.\n\"That hooded one was only pretending to sleep. Tell Saiki too.\"\nNoel nodded and gripped his axe. Lucena clutched her daggers to her chest and fell into a light sleep.\n\nAt dawn. Noel detected movement in the darkness. The hooded figure quietly rose and slipped out of the rest stop, returning shortly after. When they returned, he could see them wiping their hands on their clothes.\n\nBefore long, dawn broke.\n\nWith birdsong and morning sunlight illuminating the rest stop, Saiki opened his eyes. The mana wire's sensation had faded — its effect had expired. His body felt light. A full night's sleep had completely restored his mana.\n\nNoel looked toward Saiki and said briefly.\n\"...The hooded one went out once at dawn.\"\n\nLooking around, the hooded figure's spot was empty. No one knew when they had left. The swordsman was still leaning against the wall with his sword in his arms, and the peddler was packing up and preparing to depart.\n\nHallan said while watering the pack horse.\n\"...We can leave in about an hour. We'll reach Karendel today.\"",
        "user_input": "",
        "dialogues": [
          {
            "speaker": "lucena",
            "target": "noel",
            "line": "That hooded one was only pretending to sleep. Tell Saiki too.",
